  "_doc": "Trails of Orford-sur-le-Lac. One Feature per segment. Each Feature has a LineString geometry (an array of [lng, lat] pairs — note: longitude FIRST, that's the GeoJSON spec) and properties { name, color, condition?, kind?, parent? }. The optional 'condition' tells the renderer how usable the segment is — supported values: 'rough' (exists but not officially maintained — drawn as a dashed line, labelled 'Broussailleux'). The optional 'kind' tags the segment — 'access' marks a way to get on/off the trail (e.g. from a residential street). The optional 'parent' (used with kind:access) names the main trail this access belongs to, so the access stays visible when its parent is selected in the map filter. Edit this file in geojson.io for a visual editor.",
